text:
My first time trying out the food from this stall.

The pork chop was nice and tender and tasted great.

The 2 vegetables that I ordered were also good and had the crunch in them
Bought 1 meat, 1 steam egg and cabbage which cost $5.20. Seems pricy than normal mixed veg food stall. Will rather look for other stalls next time if going to eat around here.

Not sure what to eat on a Saturday afternoon so joined the queue to buy the economical rice from this stall and was very happy with my choice :-)

The dishes are well prepared and not salty.

The price is also reasonable to me.  Ordered 2 meat dishes, 1 vegetable & a Tao Pok it costs about $5, the portion is good too.
Choose a number of portions to add to the plate, with steamed or fried rice, all hot and delicious, for less than $10. Closes at 8pm so go early.
Located at the corner of Food Tots coffee shop in Tampines Central. Taste suit me and it taste like home cook food.  Crowded during meal time and have many tables for dinning-in.
